Write the isClosed method in the NurbsCurve class.
Remember to respond with a snippet in the form of the following:
```
class NurbsCurve {
    isClosed() {
        // your code here
    }
}
```

```javascript
class NurbsCurve {
    isClosed() {
        const firstKnot = this.knotVector[this.degree];
        const lastKnot = this.knotVector[this.knotVector.length - this.degree - 1];
        return firstKnot === lastKnot;
    }
}
```
